@node "Main" "UserInfo.amybw VER: 2.2 (12.09.97) "

 This script for AmyBw needs rexxreqtools.library and amigaguide.library

 Command: SYS:RexxC/rx AmyBW:Scripts/UserInfo.amybw @W
    File: T:AmyBW.temp
   Write: Y
  Header: Y
  Reload: N

This is an example guide to see how the AmyBW userinfo script works.
When you are reading a message of someone and want to know more about
this person you just have to start the userinfoscript in AmyBW. If the
user is in this guide you will see his info if not you will see the
index.

This guide is a special version created out of the AMBBS userguide and
Foxhunt userguide. The text is in Dutch but that should be no problem
for testing it.

Only one thing is really important about the format of this document
and that is that the nodename has to be in a specific format. It is
the first letter of the firstname followed by an underscore and the
lastname. Everything must be in CAPITALS! The name used must be the
one that is used in the messageheader.

Note that the pictures are not included in this archive.

Click @{"here" link "USERLIST" 0} to see the userlist.

@{"Credits" link "CREDITS" 0}

@endnode

