 @{"Ā Ā" link "L_MAKKINK" 0}  Leon Makkink

 (*) = Nieuw in de lijst.          (+) = Aanpassing van de lijst.
@endnode
@node "CREDITS" "Who are to blame for this thing?"

First there was an Amiga Magazine BBS userslist (guide) created by
Robert Guezen.

Leon Makkink, the author of AmyBW, created the first AmyBW script to
jump to this guide from AmyBW. He had some problems with different
versions of AmigaGuide and Multiview so he decided to use
Amigaguide.library directly.

Soon a script for Spot was created by someone else (Robert
Nienkemper?) And some time later a Thor version was created (I think I
made it myself).

This version of the userinfo script is basically the same as the one
created by Leon. I just translated it into english.


Who am I? I am @{"ĀJos van OijenĀ" link "J_VANOIJEN" 0} programmer of AmyBW 2.15.
You can contact me on jvo@xs4all.nl or on Fido 2:284/613.0


@endnode
